    {
      "title": "Solve the equation",
      "content": "Expand: $x^2+x-56=4x^2-28x$. Move all terms to one side: $-3x^2+29x-56=0$ (so $a=-3$, $b=29$)."
    },
    {
      "title": "Sum the solutions",
      "content": "By Vieta's, sum $=-b/a=-29/(-3)=\\dfrac{29}{3}$.<br/><br/>The answer is <strong>29/3</strong>.",
      "desmosExpressions": [
        "y = x(x + 1) - 56",
        "y = 4x(x - 7)"
      ]
    }
  ]
